During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed various topics including the President's upcoming foreign trip, the Vice President's meetings on Capitol Hill, the President's Cabinet's activities, the firing of former National Security Advisor Michael Flynn, the President's decision on the Paris Climate Agreement, and other domestic and international matters. Spicer also addressed questions about the relationship between the President and his National Security Advisor, the investigation into possible collusion between the Trump campaign and Russia, and other policy issues.